composeName

public static java.lang.String composeName(java.lang.String localname,
                                           java.lang.String ns,
                                           java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> namespaces,
                                           java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> namespacesToInsert)
create a qualified name from localname, ns and given namespaces bindings. If no namespace, returns localname directly. Otherwise, pre:localname is returned, where pre is taken from namespacesToInsert then if not found from namespaces, then is generated to be unique among namespaces and namespacesToInsert (always of the form nsNUMBER).

Parameters:
localname - local name
ns - namespace localname is in
namespaces - already declared namespaces
namespacesToInsert - new namespaces (IN/OUT: a new binding may be added)
Returns:
the qualified name

composeTag

public static java.lang.StringBuilder[] composeTag(XmlParsedData data,
                                                   ElementDecl elementDecl,
                                                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> namespaces,
                                                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> namespacesToInsert,
                                                   boolean withEndOfTag)
create open and close tags for an ElementDecl (with required attributes but without starting < angle bracket). if elementDecl.isEmpty, close tag will be empty and open tag will be standalone (if not html)

Parameters:
data -
elementDecl - element to create tags for
namespaces - namespaces in scope (no need to redeclare them)
namespacesToInsert - namespaces needed but not declared (will be declared)
withEndOfTag - shall the '>' be appended at the end of open tag ?
Returns:
{openTag,closeTag}
